1
00:00:01,680 --> 00:00:07,310
<b><i>At Easton Magic Academy,
each dorm is overseen by a prefect.</i></b>

2
00:00:08,650 --> 00:00:13,650
<b><i>The three prefects boasts
some of the greatest talent in Easton.</i></b>

3
00:00:13,780 --> 00:00:18,580
<b><i>All of them have the skills necessary
to become a Divine Visionary.</i></b>

4
00:01:54,460 --> 00:02:01,800
<b><i>A few years ago, a tournament was held for
13-15 year olds in the middle school division.</i></b>

5
00:02:03,010 --> 00:02:07,180
<b><i>One magic user singlehandedly
overpowered all the other competitors.</i></b>

6
00:02:08,270 --> 00:02:10,020
<b><i>They had only been nine at the time.</i></b>

7
00:02:10,480 --> 00:02:13,110
<b><i>Their name was Margarette Macaron.</i></b>

8
00:02:13,360 --> 00:02:16,570
<b><i>The future prefect of Orca dorm.</i></b>

9
00:02:17,780 --> 00:02:20,360
<b>Well, well. If it isn't the Sword Cane...</b>

10
00:02:20,570 --> 00:02:22,530
<b>Rayne Ames.</b>

11
00:02:22,950 --> 00:02:25,040
<b>Of all people...</b>

12
00:02:25,120 --> 00:02:29,040
<b>Not only will I face Mash Burnedead,
but a Divine Visionary</b>

13
00:02:29,170 --> 00:02:31,670
<b>will also entertain me?</b>

14
00:02:38,380 --> 00:02:40,430
<b>But you are...</b>

15
00:03:48,330 --> 00:03:52,210
<b>The powerless... winter.</b>

16
00:03:59,420 --> 00:04:02,220
<b><i>What the hell is going on here?</i></b>

17
00:04:03,880 --> 00:04:07,510
<b>Not every powerful magic user
strives to be a Divine Visionary.</b>

18
00:04:07,850 --> 00:04:11,270
<b>"Divine Visionary" is just a title, after all.</b>

19
00:04:12,140 --> 00:04:15,400
<b>Compared to myself who genuinely
sought nothing but strength,</b>

20
00:04:15,600 --> 00:04:19,070
<b>and you who sought a superficial position.</b>

21
00:04:20,650 --> 00:04:24,200
<b>Which one of us is stronger?</b>

22
00:04:31,450 --> 00:04:32,830
<b>Partisan.</b>

23
00:04:33,790 --> 00:04:35,080
<b>Sounds.</b>

24
00:04:40,000 --> 00:04:42,050
<b>Okay, I'll roll first.</b>

25
00:04:44,800 --> 00:04:46,680
<b>A 67.</b>

26
00:04:49,970 --> 00:04:51,470
<b>Let's see...</b>

27
00:04:51,560 --> 00:04:57,940
<b>"Easily duped by a scheming beauty's
charm spell. Lose five million Lond."</b>

28
00:04:58,190 --> 00:05:00,820
<b>What the hell!?
This board game's a piece of crap!</b>

29
00:05:02,190 --> 00:05:03,900
<b>Oh, no!</b>

30
00:05:04,320 --> 00:05:06,530
<b>I'm next.</b>

31
00:05:08,200 --> 00:05:10,080
<b>A 25.</b>

32
00:05:12,410 --> 00:05:16,870
<b>"Head to holding cell for restraining
a love interest like a stalker."</b>

33
00:05:17,370 --> 00:05:19,590
<b>"Skip 320 turns."</b>

34
00:05:21,380 --> 00:05:26,090
<b>This board game might be dangerous
as it may predict our futures.</b>

35
00:05:27,590 --> 00:05:34,230
<b>"Your little sister suddenly brings home
a boyfriend. Return to start"!?</b>

36
00:05:38,230 --> 00:05:42,070
<b>"Return a lost item to the police.
Earn 100 Lond."</b>

37
00:05:42,940 --> 00:05:44,070
<b>I'm glad.</b>

38
00:05:44,490 --> 00:05:47,070
<b>All right. Guess I'm next.</b>

39
00:05:48,410 --> 00:05:50,280
<b>A 98.</b>

40
00:05:52,660 --> 00:05:54,120
<b>Let's see...</b>

41
00:05:54,290 --> 00:05:57,580
<b>"It's discovered you can't use magic,
and you are executed."</b>

42
00:05:58,290 --> 00:05:59,790
<b>"Game over."</b>

43
00:06:04,340 --> 00:06:05,800
<b>Game over!?</b>

44
00:06:06,050 --> 00:06:08,970
<b>Gotta laugh. Just gotta laugh it off!</b>

45
00:06:08,970 --> 00:06:11,050
<b>What's up with this board game!?</b>

46
00:06:11,350 --> 00:06:13,560
<b>- Graviole. Graviole. Graviole.
- Just let 'em try!</b>

47
00:06:13,640 --> 00:06:16,310
<b>- Graviole. Graviole. Graviole.
- Yeah, let 'em try!</b>

48
00:06:16,520 --> 00:06:19,310
<b>- Graviole. Graviole. Graviole.
- Just let 'em try!</b>

49
00:06:20,150 --> 00:06:24,190
<b><i>I never dreamed he'd be surrounded
by such wonderful friends.</i></b>

50
00:06:24,980 --> 00:06:28,110
<b><i>I hope it lasts forever.</i></b>

51
00:06:29,280 --> 00:06:31,990
<b><i>I'm sure it will.</i></b>

52
00:06:33,030 --> 00:06:36,950
<b>- I'm the future wife, you hear?
- More like, what the hell is this thing!?</b>

53
00:06:34,790 --> 00:06:36,450
<b>I have to keep it going.</b>

54
00:06:37,790 --> 00:06:39,000
<b>Partisan!</b>

55
00:06:40,420 --> 00:06:42,000
<b>Shiver Sounds!</b>

56
00:06:46,050 --> 00:06:47,760
<b>Howling Sounds!</b>

57
00:07:00,690 --> 00:07:03,270
<b>I wouldn't attack if I were you.</b>

58
00:07:04,060 --> 00:07:07,860
<b>They'll explode in response
to your spellcasting.</b>

59
00:07:09,360 --> 00:07:11,030
<b>Rayne Ames.</b>

60
00:07:11,780 --> 00:07:16,290
<b>Do you know why we desire stimulation?</b>

61
00:07:16,830 --> 00:07:23,130
<b>Art, love, sports, drinking,
drugs, gambling...</b>

62
00:07:23,330 --> 00:07:28,050
<b>None of these things are necessary
to live a normal life.</b>

63
00:07:28,170 --> 00:07:30,010
<b>So why seek them?</b>

64
00:07:31,090 --> 00:07:33,180
<b>The answer is simple.</b>

65
00:07:33,970 --> 00:07:37,140
<b>Because boredom is as good as death.</b>

66
00:07:39,850 --> 00:07:43,560
<b>We live for those stimulations.</b>

67
00:07:44,190 --> 00:07:46,110
<b>Yet, you...</b>

68
00:07:46,480 --> 00:07:50,320
<b>You're awfully easygoing,
meddling in other's business.</b>

69
00:07:52,320 --> 00:07:53,950
<b>How boring.</b>

70
00:07:54,910 --> 00:07:59,830
<b>I can't imagine someone with values
like you could ever fulfill me.</b>

71
00:08:00,080 --> 00:08:02,120
<b>Be a dear and step aside.</b>

72
00:08:02,210 --> 00:08:05,580
<b>I've got to see Mash Burnedead.</b>

73
00:08:06,380 --> 00:08:08,590
<b>He's a brazen kid.</b>

74
00:08:09,300 --> 00:08:12,260
<b>Brazen enough to tell me...</b>

75
00:08:12,970 --> 00:08:16,600
<b>that he will become a Divine Visionary
even without magic.</b>

76
00:08:17,100 --> 00:08:19,850
<b>That he will change the perception
of this world.</b>

77
00:08:23,890 --> 00:08:26,610
<b><i>His mood shifted?</i></b>

78
00:08:27,150 --> 00:08:32,280
<b>If he went against Margarette, not even
Lord Rayne would walk away unscathed.</b>

79
00:08:33,900 --> 00:08:38,410
<b>Rayne may act aloof,
but he always takes care of others.</b>

80
00:08:38,830 --> 00:08:40,660
<b>By the way, Nerey...</b>

81
00:08:40,830 --> 00:08:44,250
<b>What do you know about marks?</b>

82
00:08:44,580 --> 00:08:50,170
<b>Well, the number of marks increases
in accordance with your absolute magic power?</b>

83
00:08:50,250 --> 00:08:51,630
<b>Correct.</b>

84
00:08:51,800 --> 00:08:58,760
<b>Easton Magic Academy has had
many double-liners cross our step, of course.</b>

85
00:08:59,180 --> 00:09:04,440
<b>But there have only been an extremely
small number of triple-liners.</b>

86
00:09:05,020 --> 00:09:09,770
<b>If two lines means magic itself
recognizes their talent,</b>

87
00:09:09,770 --> 00:09:13,530
<b>then those with three lines
must be chosen by the gods.</b>

88
00:09:13,990 --> 00:09:17,160
<b>The summer... of bliss.</b>

89
00:09:17,660 --> 00:09:22,660
<b>And the youngest to ever
acquire three lines is...</b>

90
00:09:23,330 --> 00:09:26,540
<b>the one named Rayne Ames.</b>

91
00:09:27,040 --> 00:09:29,590
<b>Change the perception of this world...</b>

92
00:09:29,790 --> 00:09:34,470
<b>I'll make sure that brazen kid
goes as far as he can go.</b>

93
00:09:37,470 --> 00:09:40,640
<b>"It's discovered
you can't use magic. Executed."</b>

94
00:09:44,020 --> 00:09:46,270
<b>I'm gonna get some fresh air.</b>

95
00:09:47,440 --> 00:09:51,650
<b>He acts cool,
but it must be eating him up inside.</b>

96
00:09:51,650 --> 00:09:55,490
<b>Of course it is.
He didn't do anything wrong.</b>

97
00:09:55,490 --> 00:09:59,990
<b>If I were in his shoes,
I would keep blaming society.</b>

98
00:10:11,340 --> 00:10:13,460
<b>No one will ever spot me out here.</b>

99
00:10:14,960 --> 00:10:19,010
<b>I can't eat this specialty cream puff
in everyone's presence.</b>

100
00:10:25,310 --> 00:10:29,190
<b><i>A triple-liner. A talent gifted by the gods.</i></b>

101
00:10:29,940 --> 00:10:33,690
<b><i>To find someone my age
who's achieved that level.</i></b>

102
00:10:34,780 --> 00:10:37,700
<b><i>Just how blessed am I?</i></b>

103
00:10:38,610 --> 00:10:43,160
<b><i>Howling Sounds will create a chain explosion
in reaction to chanting.</i></b>

104
00:10:43,450 --> 00:10:48,960
<b><i>He may be a triple-liner,
but he has to chant to use magic.</i></b>

105
00:10:49,160 --> 00:10:51,540
<b>Orter Madl put you up to this, didn't he?</b>

106
00:10:52,420 --> 00:10:56,710
<b>It's not like you to take an interest
in school affairs, but you're here.</b>

107
00:10:56,840 --> 00:10:59,510
<b>This pretty much has to be
Orter Madl's doing.</b>

108
00:10:59,510 --> 00:11:02,470
<b>Dear me. I have no idea
what you're talking about.</b>

109
00:11:04,510 --> 00:11:08,600
<b>Your target Mash Burnedead
can't use magic.</b>

110
00:11:10,600 --> 00:11:15,440
<b>In this world, lack of magic
is basically having no human rights.</b>

111
00:11:15,770 --> 00:11:18,690
<b>An ordinary human
would feel despair, no doubt.</b>

112
00:11:19,450 --> 00:11:23,990
<b>Jealous of those who can use magic,
regretting being ever born, hating society...</b>

113
00:11:23,990 --> 00:11:26,580
<b>All of those would be reasonable reactions.</b>

114
00:11:27,370 --> 00:11:31,330
<b>But Mash Burnedead is different.</b>

115
00:11:32,040 --> 00:11:33,130
<b>He...</b>

116
00:11:34,340 --> 00:11:38,130
<b>fights against his own destiny.</b>

117
00:11:42,010 --> 00:11:46,350
<b>Not that an underhanded rat like you
would ever understand.</b>

118
00:11:47,140 --> 00:11:50,140
<b>Oh my. What a darling little speech.</b>

119
00:11:51,560 --> 00:11:52,650
<b>But...</b>

120
00:11:53,730 --> 00:11:56,860
<b>I couldn't care less.</b>

121
00:11:59,110 --> 00:12:03,030
<b><i>They remain confident despite facing down
a triple-liner Divine Visionary.</i></b>

122
00:12:03,200 --> 00:12:06,280
<b><i>They're not being cocky, though.</i></b>

123
00:12:06,700 --> 00:12:10,080
<b><i>They distributed their coins to the dorm, saying
they weren't interested in Divine Visionaries.</i></b>

124
00:12:10,080 --> 00:12:16,670
<b><i>But they took a total of ten gold coins
from upperclassmen, more than anyone last year.</i></b>

125
00:12:17,040 --> 00:12:22,050
<b><i>Besides, Howling Sounds will end
the moment he chants a counterspell.</i></b>

126
00:12:22,630 --> 00:12:27,390
<b><i>This shows Margarette Macaron's
overwhelming talent.</i></b>

127
00:12:37,150 --> 00:12:41,360
<b>I hear it... The unending applause...</b>

128
00:12:47,910 --> 00:12:50,200
<b>Sounds Orchestra.</b>

129
00:12:54,210 --> 00:12:57,330
<b>Now you're forced to cast a spell.</b>

130
00:12:57,670 --> 00:12:58,790
<b>Checkmate.</b>

131
00:12:59,130 --> 00:13:05,050
<b>Um... What exactly distinguishes
a triple-liner from a double-liner?</b>

132
00:13:05,180 --> 00:13:09,430
<b>Three lines signify one chosen by the gods.</b>

133
00:13:09,890 --> 00:13:15,690
<b>They can unleash more power
than a double-liner, of course.</b>

134
00:13:15,850 --> 00:13:18,400
<b>But that is hardly all they can do.</b>

135
00:13:18,980 --> 00:13:24,200
<b>They can awaken
a wand's dormant true form.</b>

136
00:13:24,610 --> 00:13:26,200
<b>True form?</b>

137
00:13:26,410 --> 00:13:32,080
<b>Yes, that's correct. The reason why
lies behind magic being a gift from the gods.</b>

138
00:13:42,170 --> 00:13:45,590
<b><i>Howling Sounds was drowned out
without being activated?</i></b>

139
00:13:45,670 --> 00:13:47,720
<b>Summon Ares.</b>

140
00:13:47,970 --> 00:13:53,350
<b>In other words, their power calls upon
a god's strength from within a wand.</b>

141
00:13:53,970 --> 00:13:56,850
<b><i>His wand is changing form!?</i></b>

142
00:13:57,190 --> 00:14:02,610
<b><i>So this is what was given to Divine Visionary
Rayne Ames, the title of a god's wand...</i></b>

143
00:14:03,360 --> 00:14:05,030
<b>"Sword Cane."</b>

144
00:14:05,280 --> 00:14:06,490
<b>Checkmate.</b>

145
00:14:06,610 --> 00:14:08,320
<b>Black Partisan.</b>

146
00:14:13,410 --> 00:14:15,040
<b>Sounds Shield!</b>

147
00:14:29,970 --> 00:14:34,180
<b>U-Um, I guess I should say thanks.</b>

148
00:14:34,470 --> 00:14:39,690
<b>For what? I was just playing
with some rabbits in the forest.</b>

149
00:14:40,770 --> 00:14:43,690
<b>So you are a fan of rabbits.</b>

150
00:14:45,230 --> 00:14:47,320
<b>The selection exam is soon.</b>

151
00:14:47,320 --> 00:14:48,450
<b>Yes.</b>

152
00:14:48,900 --> 00:14:51,660
<b>I'm terrible at encouraging people.</b>

153
00:14:51,910 --> 00:14:54,950
<b>But I'll say one thing.</b>

154
00:14:55,740 --> 00:14:59,830
<b>You're embarking on a challenge the likes
of which this world has never seen.</b>

155
00:15:00,290 --> 00:15:03,500
<b>Nothing good will ever come
from your failure.</b>

156
00:15:05,630 --> 00:15:06,800
<b>So win.</b>

157
00:15:06,800 --> 00:15:09,590
<b>And give your challenge meaning.</b>

158
00:15:10,970 --> 00:15:12,340
<b>'Kay.</b>

159
00:15:17,100 --> 00:15:19,850
<b>You kids are so sloppy.</b>

160
00:15:21,190 --> 00:15:23,060
<b><i>So that's a triple-liner.</i></b>

161
00:15:23,310 --> 00:15:27,610
<b><i>The gigantic wand raises
the baseline magic power output.</i></b>

162
00:15:28,070 --> 00:15:32,950
<b><i>Even entry-level spells have the effectiveness
of Secondth magic.</i></b>

163
00:15:34,160 --> 00:15:39,750
<b><i>I could have tried my own Secondth spell,
but I put their safety as my priority.</i></b>

164
00:15:40,080 --> 00:15:42,540
<b><i>Is this maternal instinct?</i></b>

165
00:15:45,000 --> 00:15:47,960
<b>Margarette, I'm sorry.</b>

166
00:15:48,340 --> 00:15:49,590
<b>No worries.</b>

167
00:15:52,050 --> 00:15:56,260
<b>As they all say,
you save the best for last.</b>

168
00:16:01,140 --> 00:16:02,310
<b><i>Afterwards...</i></b>

169
00:16:03,350 --> 00:16:06,440
<b>These are the coins we got from Lang.</b>

170
00:16:06,520 --> 00:16:08,570
<b>Three per person sound good?</b>

171
00:16:09,190 --> 00:16:10,780
<b>Let's do our best on the selection exam.</b>

172
00:16:11,110 --> 00:16:12,660
<b>I can't!</b>

173
00:16:14,410 --> 00:16:16,660
<b>I'm sorry!</b>

174
00:16:26,250 --> 00:16:29,670
<b>It'll be soon. Wait for me, Anna.</b>

175
00:16:29,670 --> 00:16:31,170
<b>STARE</b>

176
00:16:35,050 --> 00:16:37,220
<b>I'm too hyped to sleep!</b>

177
00:16:37,300 --> 00:16:39,100
<b>Guess I'll check my luggage.</b>

178
00:16:39,430 --> 00:16:43,850
<b>Water bottle, handkerchief,
bug repellant, tissue.</b>

179
00:16:43,940 --> 00:16:48,110
<b>And then eye drops, antacid,
pain reliever, laxative.</b>

180
00:16:48,110 --> 00:16:51,610
<b>Facial toner, antiperspirant,
breath freshener.</b>

181
00:16:53,110 --> 00:16:56,490
<b>Mash, I heard from your friends.</b>

182
00:16:56,740 --> 00:17:00,740
<b>Everyone has discovered
that you can't use magic?</b>

183
00:17:02,200 --> 00:17:06,250
<b>And that you will be charged with this crime
if you don't meet their demands.</b>

184
00:17:11,300 --> 00:17:14,510
<b>I'm sorry. This is my doing.</b>

185
00:17:15,340 --> 00:17:20,510
<b>If only I could have given you a normal life.</b>

186
00:17:21,390 --> 00:17:25,390
<b>If only I could have provided you
a life without inconveniences.</b>

187
00:17:26,520 --> 00:17:29,940
<b>If I had done more to hide it all to the end.</b>

188
00:17:29,940 --> 00:17:31,440
<b>But I'm happy.</b>

189
00:17:32,900 --> 00:17:35,950
<b>I have you who always
looks out for me so much.</b>

190
00:17:36,410 --> 00:17:41,200
<b>I was able to go to school even for
a little bit, and was blessed with friends.</b>

191
00:17:42,370 --> 00:17:44,870
<b>I got to eat lots of cream puffs, too.</b>

192
00:17:46,000 --> 00:17:47,790
<b>So I'm happy.</b>

193
00:17:48,290 --> 00:17:50,290
<b>Thank you, Pops.</b>

194
00:17:54,300 --> 00:17:57,430
<b>Good. Now come back safe and sound.</b>

195
00:17:59,680 --> 00:18:04,430
<b><i>The path to Divine Visionary
is broadly divided into three stages.</i></b>

196
00:18:05,940 --> 00:18:08,190
<b><i>The first is coin acquisition.</i></b>

197
00:18:08,980 --> 00:18:12,230
<b><i>The second is
the Divine Visionary Candidate Exam.</i></b>

198
00:18:12,980 --> 00:18:16,780
<b><i>The third is
the Divine Visionary Elect Final Exam.</i></b>

199
00:18:17,530 --> 00:18:23,830
<b><i>One must acquire five or more gold coins
to advance to the second stage.</i></b>

200
00:18:23,830 --> 00:18:25,580
<b>MOORE TOMATO
LANG DORM THIRD-YEAR,
THREE GOLD COINS</b>

201
00:18:24,250 --> 00:18:28,830
<b><i>However, due to Innocent Zero's intervention,
the exam has been pushed forward.</i></b>

202
00:18:25,580 --> 00:18:27,330
<b>DOLB MARX
LANG DORM THIRD-YEAR,
THREE GOLD COINS</b>

203
00:18:25,580 --> 00:18:27,330
<b>PON TORUS
ORCA DORM SECOND-YEAR,
THREE GOLD COINS</b>

204
00:18:27,330 --> 00:18:29,080
<b>LEBLANC RUSSELL
LANG DORM SECOND-YEAR,
THREE GOLD COINS</b>

205
00:18:28,830 --> 00:18:32,840
<b><i>Only three gold coins are needed to qualify.</i></b>

206
00:18:29,080 --> 00:18:30,840
<b>MAX LAND
ADLER DORM THIRD-YEAR,
THREE GOLD COINS</b>

207
00:18:30,840 --> 00:18:32,840
<b>AORIO MORRIS
ADLER DORM THIRD-YEAR,
THREE GOLD COINS</b>

208
00:18:32,840 --> 00:18:34,590
<b>DOT BARRETT
ADLER DORM FIRST-YEAR,
THREE GOLD COINS</b>

209
00:18:34,590 --> 00:18:36,590
<b>FINN AMES
ADLER DORM FIRST-YEAR,
THREE GOLD COINS</b>

210
00:18:36,590 --> 00:18:39,760
<b>CARPACCIO LUO-YANG
ORCA DORM FIRST-YEAR,
FOUR GOLD COINS</b>

211
00:18:37,050 --> 00:18:39,760
<b><i>Magic is the crux of our society!
It is everything!</i></b>

212
00:18:39,760 --> 00:18:42,890
<b>LANCE CROWN
ADLER DORM FIRST-YEAR,
FIVE GOLD COINS</b>

213
00:18:40,300 --> 00:18:42,890
<b><i>Those without magic have no rights!</i></b>

214
00:18:42,890 --> 00:18:46,890
<b>MARGARETTE MACARON
ORCA DORM THIRD-YEAR,
FIVE GOLD COINS</b>

215
00:18:43,350 --> 00:18:46,890
<b><i>Here we have the magic users
who are the pinnacle of this society!</i></b>

216
00:18:47,230 --> 00:18:50,650
<b><i>The examinees have entered the arena!</i></b>

217
00:18:51,560 --> 00:18:56,280
<b>It seems even Margarette Macaron
will enter this year.</b>

218
00:18:56,690 --> 00:19:02,320
<b>You face a difficult road, Mash Burnedead.</b>

219
00:18:59,660 --> 00:19:02,910
<b>MASH BURNEDEAD
ADLER DORM FIRST-YEAR,
SEVEN GOLD COINS</b>

220
00:19:10,170 --> 00:19:13,420
<b>Humans are defined by a standard.</b>

221
00:19:14,040 --> 00:19:19,180
<b>Existences like you who disrupt
the entire system are not human.</b>

222
00:19:20,340 --> 00:19:26,310
<b>As long as I'm around, your existence
will never be acknowledged by this world.</b>

223
00:19:27,560 --> 00:19:29,440
<b>CLNCH CLNCH CLNCH</b>

224
00:19:29,520 --> 00:19:31,190
<b>"That's not necessarily true."</b>

225
00:19:31,350 --> 00:19:32,190
<b>"It's fine!"</b>

226
00:19:32,270 --> 00:19:33,690
<b>"You can do it if you try!"</b>

227
00:19:34,520 --> 00:19:35,440
<b>"Go for it."</b>

228
00:19:35,940 --> 00:19:42,620
<b>Thanks, Kevin, Tom, Mike, Kim,
Yamada, Koji, Satomi, Yukari.</b>

229
00:19:43,240 --> 00:19:45,030
<b>I'll do my best.</b>

230
00:19:48,580 --> 00:19:50,210
<b>I'll take you on then.</b>

231
00:19:54,630 --> 00:19:56,000
<b>With all I've got.</b>

232
00:19:59,260 --> 00:20:02,090
<b><i>Now, the last one to enter...</i></b>

233
00:20:02,470 --> 00:20:07,060
<b><i>Adler dorm, Mash Burnedead!</i></b>

234
00:20:07,600 --> 00:20:09,560
<b>Hey, that Mash guy...</b>

235
00:20:09,560 --> 00:20:12,020
<b>Isn't he the one who can't use magic?</b>

236
00:20:12,020 --> 00:20:16,570
<b>If that's true, him being
in the selection exam is unprecedented.</b>

237
00:20:16,900 --> 00:20:19,360
<b>This is no place for you!</b>

238
00:20:19,360 --> 00:20:20,570
<b>Go home!</b>

239
00:20:20,570 --> 00:20:22,320
<b>That's right, go home!</b>

240
00:20:22,450 --> 00:20:26,330
<b>Go home! Go home!</b>

241
00:20:26,410 --> 00:20:30,200
<b>Go home! Go home!</b>

242
00:20:30,290 --> 00:20:32,330
<b>Go home!</b>

243
00:20:32,580 --> 00:20:38,340
<b>Come on! Someone like him might ruin
the prestige of Divine Visionaries!</b>

244
00:20:38,750 --> 00:20:42,090
<b>What do you say about that, admins!?</b>

245
00:20:42,260 --> 00:20:44,760
<b>What a bunch of bullies.</b>

246
00:20:44,930 --> 00:20:49,100
<b>Mash earned the right
to be here by winning coins.</b>

247
00:20:49,890 --> 00:20:53,560
<b><i>His entire life is riding
on the results of this exam.</i></b>

248
00:20:53,690 --> 00:20:57,060
<b><i>Mash must be under incredible pressure.</i></b>

249
00:20:57,060 --> 00:20:58,690
<b><i>I should be encouraging.</i></b>

250
00:20:59,480 --> 00:21:02,360
<b>Mash, you don't have to worry...</b>

251
00:21:02,360 --> 00:21:05,610
<b>HONK</b>

252
00:21:04,200 --> 00:21:05,610
<b>I wanna go home.</b>

253
00:21:05,820 --> 00:21:07,700
<b>I don't blame you.</b>

254
00:21:08,950 --> 00:21:11,700
<b><i>Adler, Lang, Orca.</i></b>

255
00:21:11,700 --> 00:21:15,370
<b><i>All 12 candidates
from the three dorms are here!</i></b>

256
00:21:16,080 --> 00:21:18,460
<b><i>Let's get right to it then!</i></b>

257
00:21:18,460 --> 00:21:20,460
<b><i>Elimination's the name of the game!</i></b>

258
00:21:20,460 --> 00:21:23,090
<b><i>What better way to do that
than with a survival match!</i></b>

259
00:21:23,090 --> 00:21:27,140
<b><i>So we made a dead-or-alive
qualifying exam for you!</i></b>

260
00:21:28,300 --> 00:21:31,020
<b><i>It's called, "Deadervant's Haunt"!</i></b>

261
00:21:32,220 --> 00:21:33,480
<b><i>The rules are simple!</i></b>

262
00:21:33,480 --> 00:21:37,190
<b><i>Find a key hidden somewhere
in this stage and escape!</i></b>

263
00:21:37,190 --> 00:21:39,820
<b>Huh? That doesn't sound
as dangerous as I thought.</b>

264
00:21:39,820 --> 00:21:43,360
<b><i>But! The key is in the swim bladder
of a Troll-goosefish!</i></b>

265
00:21:43,360 --> 00:21:47,280
<b><i>You must use magic
to pop it like a balloon!</i></b>

266
00:21:48,570 --> 00:21:52,500
<b>That's really tough. I see.
So that's what this test's about.</b>

267
00:21:52,500 --> 00:21:53,950
<b><i>Furthermore...</i></b>

268
00:21:54,910 --> 00:21:58,460
<b><i>You'll be on the run
from three Deadervants all the while!</i></b>

269
00:21:58,460 --> 00:22:00,210
<b>WAIL</b>

270
00:22:00,750 --> 00:22:02,710
<b>Monsters!</b>

271
00:22:02,710 --> 00:22:04,090
<b><i>Yes, monsters.</i></b>

272
00:23:35,350 --> 00:23:40,060
<b>NEXT EPISODE
MASH BURNEDEAD AND THE BRAWNY BALLOON</b>

